Mods.push({
"name": "False Red Lizard [Downpour Version]",
"id": "fakereddownpour",
"workshop_id": "3620854810",
"author": "VoidVortex",
"desc": "I HAVEN'T ACTUALLY TESTED IT, BUT THIS MOD IS LIKELY TO CRASH WITHOUT DOWNPOUR INSTALLED.<br>For the vanilla-specific version, check out this link: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3606562756&searchtext=false+red+lizard<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br><br>TLDR: Pink lizard that looks like a red lizard. Other creatures interact with it as if it was a red lizard, plus some extra interactions. Mostly found at Outskirts and Industrial Complex.<br><br><br><br><br>This mod adds a new lizard to the game, that is, the false red lizard!<br><br>Devious, territorial, and with a good sense of self-preservation.<br><br>Similarly to some creatures in real life, these lizards borrow the reputation of another well-known denizen of Rain World in order to increase their own odds of survival. Generally, their relations with other creatures are the same as that of red lizards, which means that other lizards will respect false red lizards and won't be nearly as snappy to them. However, their physical prowess and abilities are the same as those of a humble pink lizard.<br><br>They do have some unique key interactions, differing from true red lizards:<br><br>-False red lizards are just as territorial as true red lizards, which means that like them, they will immediately go hostile against members of their own species. Unlike most creatures, they can tell each other apart from actual red lizards.<br><br>-True red lizards, however, can't differentiate a false red from their own, so they will try to kill them on sight as they would with other true reds. The false red will do its best to flee instead, as it very well knows it can't win the fight.<br><br>-While a true red lizard is able to fight back vultures, a false red lizard won't try, and so it will flee like normal.<br><br>This mod comes together with all the necessary spawns to add false red lizards to the Downpour experience, which means that upon installing the mod, players can start a new save and they will soon see the new lizard in their game.<br>The populations are most dense in regions like Outskirts and Industrial Complex, but some can be seen in Industrial Complex as well. If pink lizards thrive in a region, chances are the similarly-built false red will too! The mod includes the false red lizard in lineages thorought the game, so not many will be seen right away, but there's a few assured spawns here and there.<br><br>Notes on Saint:<br>In Saint's campaign, pink lizards are completely extinct. Evolutionary speaking, it only makes sense that another creature that is basically the same thing but able to camouflage itself as a mighty red lizard would end up phasing them out, meaning that they are much more common in that campaign. This is also an excuse to be incredibly evil and shufle several false reds with the two real reds of Outskirts and Industrial Complex. :)<br><br>False red lizards should be compatible with most mods as long as they don't heavily edit spawns in Vanilla regions or add a lot of rooms to them. I'd be thankful if people who find any incompatibilities notified me on the comments so that I can make a list of known incompatibilities in the near future. While I don't plan on adding any actual extra content not related to false red lizards in this mod, I will do my best to fix any bugs that may arise and to keep up with Rain World's updates. Eventually, I will be making it so Lizard Customizer isn't required for the mod to work. Thank you for trying out my mod!",
"thumb": "previews/3620854810.png",
"url": "https://andrew.fm/rainworld/raindb/False_Red_Lizard_Downpour_Version.zip",
"requirements": "lizardcustomizer,moreslugcats",
"version": "1.0",
"created": 1765301989,
"modified": 1765301989,
"tags": "Creatures",
"order": 3852
});

